#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kalzium;"
msgstr "Korištenje &kalzium;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview of &kalzium; usage"
msgstr "Pregled korištenja &kalzium;-a"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kalzium; is very easy to use. It is specially designed for students of all "
"ages to use as a small and quick database."
msgstr ""
"&kalzium; je jako lak za korištenje. Specijalno je dizajniran za studente "
"svih godina kao mala i brza baza podataka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a screenshot of &kalzium; in action:"
msgstr "Ovo je slika ekrana &kalziuma;-a u akciji:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kalzium; main screen, immediately after the first start"
msgstr "&kalzium; glavni ekran, odmah nakon pokretanja"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kalzium; main screen"
msgstr "&kalzium; glavni ekran"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "The information dialog"
msgstr "Informacijski dijalog"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The information dialog is accessed by clicking with the &LMB; on any "
"element. This is the place to get information about an element. With the "
"buttons at the bottom of the dialog you can change the element which is "
"displayed without closing the dialog."
msgstr ""
"Do informacijskog dijaloga možete doći klikom sa &LMB; na bilo koji element. "
"Ovo je mjesto za dobijanje informacija o elementu. Sa dugmadima na dnu "
"dijaloga možete pormijeniti elemnt koji je prikazan bez zatvaranja dijaloga."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Data Overview"
msgstr "Prikaz podataka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Data Overview</guilabel> page tells you about different facts "
"related to the element."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Prikaz podataka</guilabel> stranica govori vam o različitim "
"činjenicama vezanim za element."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the data available in &kalzium; you will see different radii of "
"the element. The covalent radius is the radius of a non charged atom of the "
"element in a molecule. The could for example be the O-H-distance in Water. "
"The atomic radius is the radius of an elemental atom, &eg; not bound to "
"anything. The van der Waals-radius is defined as the distance of two atoms "
"of the same sort in two equal molecules, for example two carbon-atoms in "
"propane. The last possible radius is the ionic radius including its charge."
msgstr ""
"U zavisnosti od dostupnih podataka u &kalzium;-u vidjet ćete različite "
"radijuse elemenata. Kovalentni radijus je radijus neutralnog atoma elementa "
"u molekuli. Na primijer ovo može biti O-H udaljenost u Vodi. Atomski radijus "
"je radijus elemntarnog atoma, &eg; koji ije vezan ni za šta. Van Der Waals- "
"radijus je definisan kao razmak dva atoma iste vrste u dvije jednake "
"molekule, naprimjer dva atoma karbona u propanu. Zadnji mogući radijus je "
"ionski radijus koji uključuje njegovo naelektrisanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The mass of an element is the average mass of all isotopes in relation to "
"their percentage."
msgstr ""
"Masa elemenata je srednja masa svih izotopa u relaciji sa njihovim procentom."

